    <div class="problem-header">
      <span class="label-pill">The free keyword research workflow</span>
      <h2 class="h-lg">5 steps. 30–45 minutes. <span class="accent">10–15 validated keywords.</span></h2>
      <p>This workflow combines free tools to approximate what paid tools do. Follow it in order.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="ba-grid">
      <div class="ba-col after" style="grid-column: 1 / -1;">
        <ul class="ba-list">
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Find opportunities: Google Search Console → filter positions 8–20</h4>
              <p>If you have an existing site, start here. Pages ranking in positions 8–20 need a content update or internal link, not a new article. Easiest wins first.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Generate ideas: AnswerThePublic + Soovle → export both lists</h4>
              <p>Enter your main topic in both tools. Export the question-based results from AnswerThePublic and the multi-platform autocomplete from Soovle. Combine into one list.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Validate volume: Google Keyword Planner + Keyword Surfer</h4>
              <p>Cross-reference your shortlist in Keyword Planner for volume ranges. Keyword Surfer shows volume directly in Google while you search. Any keyword with volume in 1K+ range is worth targeting.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">04</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Assess difficulty: Ahrefs Free Keyword Generator → focus on KD under 20</h4>
              <p>Run your validated shortlist through Ahrefs Free. Keywords with KD under 20 are winnable for new or small sites without building backlinks. Drop anything KD 30+ from your immediate target list.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
          <li>
            <span class="ba-num">05</span>
            <div>
              <h4>Map to content: one primary keyword + 3–5 secondary per article</h4>
              <p>Assign keywords to content rather than targeting one per page. Prevents cannibalization and builds topical depth. Plan 10–15 articles from each research session.</p>
            </div>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

